# CODEOWNERS - Define code ownership for automated review requests
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Each line is a file pattern followed by one or more owners.
# Order matters - later patterns override earlier ones.
# Owners can be @usernames, @org/team-names, or email addresses.
#
# See docs/CODEOWNERS_PATTERNS.md for advanced usage examples.

# =============================================================================
# DEFAULT OWNERS
# =============================================================================
# These owners will be requested for review when no other pattern matches.
# Uncomment and customize:

# * @your-username
# * @your-org/core-team

# =============================================================================
# DIRECTORY OWNERSHIP
# =============================================================================

# Source code
# /src/                     @your-org/dev-team

# API layer
# /src/api/                 @your-org/api-team
# /src/graphql/             @your-org/api-team

# Frontend
# /src/components/          @your-org/frontend-team
# /src/pages/               @your-org/frontend-team
# /src/styles/              @your-org/frontend-team

# Backend
# /src/services/            @your-org/backend-team
# /src/models/              @your-org/backend-team

# Infrastructure
# /infra/                   @your-org/platform-team
# /terraform/               @your-org/platform-team
# /k8s/                     @your-org/platform-team

# Documentation
# /docs/                    @your-org/docs-team

# =============================================================================
# LANGUAGE-SPECIFIC OWNERSHIP
# =============================================================================

# JavaScript/TypeScript
# *.js                      @your-org/js-team
# *.jsx                     @your-org/js-team
# *.ts                      @your-org/js-team
# *.tsx                     @your-org/js-team

# Python
# *.py                      @your-org/python-team

# Go
# *.go                      @your-org/go-team

# Rust
# *.rs                      @your-org/rust-team

# =============================================================================
# CONFIGURATION FILES
# =============================================================================

# Package managers
# package.json              @your-org/dev-team
# package-lock.json         @your-org/dev-team
# pnpm-lock.yaml            @your-org/dev-team
# yarn.lock                 @your-org/dev-team
# requirements.txt          @your-org/dev-team
# go.mod                    @your-org/dev-team
# Cargo.toml                @your-org/dev-team

# Build configuration
# Dockerfile                @your-org/platform-team
# docker-compose*.yml       @your-org/platform-team
# Makefile                  @your-org/platform-team

# Linting and formatting
# .eslintrc*                @your-org/dev-team
# .prettierrc*              @your-org/dev-team
# .editorconfig             @your-org/dev-team

# =============================================================================
# CI/CD AND DEVOPS
# =============================================================================

# GitHub Actions
# /.github/                 @your-org/devops-team
# /.github/workflows/       @your-org/devops-team

# Deployment configurations
# /.github/workflows/deploy* @your-org/platform-team @your-org/security-team

# =============================================================================
# SECURITY-SENSITIVE FILES
# =============================================================================
# These patterns ensure security team reviews sensitive changes

# Security configurations
# /security/                @your-org/security-team
# **/security/              @your-org/security-team

# Authentication and authorization
# /src/auth/                @your-org/security-team
# **/auth/**                @your-org/security-team
# **/authentication/**      @your-org/security-team
# **/authorization/**       @your-org/security-team

# Secrets and environment templates
# *.env.example             @your-org/security-team
# .env.template             @your-org/security-team

# Cryptography
# **/crypto/**              @your-org/security-team
# **/encryption/**          @your-org/security-team

# Dependency lockfiles (supply chain security)
# package-lock.json         @your-org/security-team
# pnpm-lock.yaml            @your-org/security-team
# yarn.lock                 @your-org/security-team
# requirements.txt          @your-org/security-team
# Pipfile.lock              @your-org/security-team
# poetry.lock               @your-org/security-team
# go.sum                    @your-org/security-team
# Cargo.lock                @your-org/security-team
# Gemfile.lock              @your-org/security-team

# GitHub repository settings
# CODEOWNERS                @your-org/security-team @your-org/admin-team
# SECURITY.md               @your-org/security-team

# =============================================================================
# CRITICAL FILES (Multiple Approvers)
# =============================================================================
# These files require approval from multiple teams

# Release configuration
# /release/                 @your-org/dev-team @your-org/devops-team

# Database migrations
# /migrations/              @your-org/backend-team @your-org/dba-team
# **/migrations/**          @your-org/backend-team @your-org/dba-team

# API contracts/schemas
# /openapi/                 @your-org/api-team @your-org/frontend-team
# **/schemas/               @your-org/api-team

# =============================================================================
# LEGAL AND COMPLIANCE
# =============================================================================

# LICENSE*                  @your-org/legal-team
# NOTICE*                   @your-org/legal-team
# COPYRIGHT*                @your-org/legal-team
# PATENTS*                  @your-org/legal-team

# =============================================================================
# GLOB PATTERN EXAMPLES
# =============================================================================
# These are commented examples showing glob pattern capabilities

# Match files in root only (not subdirectories)
# /*.md                     @your-org/docs-team

# Match files anywhere in the repo
# **/README.md              @your-org/docs-team

# Match specific file types in specific directories
# /src/**/*.test.ts         @your-org/qa-team
# /src/**/*.spec.ts         @your-org/qa-team

# Exclude patterns (use later rules to override)
# /tests/                   @your-org/qa-team
# /tests/fixtures/          @your-org/dev-team  # Override: fixtures owned by dev

# =============================================================================
# TEAM HIERARCHY EXAMPLE
# =============================================================================
# Demonstrate escalation patterns

# Base ownership
# /src/                     @your-org/dev-team

# Specialized sub-ownership (overrides base)
# /src/core/                @your-org/core-team

# Critical core modules (most specific wins)
# /src/core/engine/         @your-org/core-team @your-org/architecture-team
